data.name: Pork Tenderloin with Apple Cider Glaze
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy pork tenderloin drizzled with a sweet and tangy apple cider glaze, perfect for a comforting dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small saucepan, combine apple cider, brown sugar, soy sauce, minced garlic, and thyme. Bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves. Cook for about 10 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Season the pork tenderloin with salt and pepper.
In a large oven-safe skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Sear the pork on all sides until golden brown, about 3-4 minutes per side.
Pour the apple cider glaze over the seared pork in the skillet.
Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature of the pork reaches 145째F (63째C).
Remove from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve the sliced pork tenderloin drizzled with the apple cider glaze.
data.detailedName: Oven-Roasted Pork Tenderloin with Sweet Apple Cider Glaze
